Steve K
In reply to this message
Cut into cheese train size pieces, like sugar cube size. Then I put them in a cheese cloth and hang them. Jumble them once a day so all sides get air. You can also just put them on a plate and cover with a cloth napkin. Whatever works. I just try to avoid moisture on them so too much mold doesn't grow.
